Gauteng police have warned resident to be vigilant as a man posing as an officer has attempted to solicit money from unsuspecting victims. JOHANNESBURG Gauteng police have issued a warning about a man who is been posing as a police officer to solicit money from complainants.It s understood that he contacts police stations in the province demanding names of arrested suspects, claiming that he wants to profile them.The police s Kay Makhubela says the man subsequently calls complainants and requests money in order to update them about their cases. He is using different kinds of people who are known in the police service, so we have advised the victims not to take any information from a stranger and not to give anyone information through the phone. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)